{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\n\nrebar's authenticated-authorship capability is fully built and merged (identity epic\ngnu-whale-ichor / e68d, foundation 2fd4, op-cert asymmetric 6d0d), and the HMAC->sshsig\nattestation migration completed cleanly on 2026-07-14. But the LAST MILE — turning on\nevent-authorship signing so `identity.require_authenticated` can be flipped to `true` —\nwas deferred out of every build epic into the parked idea a422 (dated-circular-velvetworm)\nand never executed. Post-mortem findings this epic remediates:\n\n- **Local sessions/worktrees on this machine** have no persistent signing key (no\n  `identity.signing_key`, no `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY`, no `.rebar/current_identity`);\n  only ~4 one-off validation-demo signed events exist store-wide vs ~5,000 unsigned.\n- **GitHub Actions** (`.github/workflows/reconcile-bridge.yml`) already has the full\n  key-materialize + job-level env wiring (story 9e76/cc0b) but is secret-gated: with\n  `REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY` unset it writes UNSIGNED (advisory). Exactly one CI-authored\n  signed event exists store-wide.\n- **Gerrit-side operations** (review-bot signing 245e, reconciler inline-sign 9e76,\n  opcert-service) landed in code, but the post-deploy validation canary 1787 was\n  FORCE-CLOSED \"pending post-deploy run\" — never confirmed to sign on the deployed VM.\n- **The guardrail** bug 27ae made the merge-gate config-driven and set an `enforce_since`\n  grandfather boundary; the perf blocker 1cc0 is fixed. Flipping the flag today would fail\n  every push because the store is unsigned — the flip must land AFTER every writer signs,\n  in the same change that pins `enforce_since`.\n\nThis epic supersedes a422 and drives the rollout to the point where\n`identity.require_authenticated = true` can be enabled with NOTHING failing on any writer\nsurface.\n\n## Scope / planned child stories\n\n1. **Local machine signing** — provision a persistent signing key for local\n   worktrees/sessions (per-machine `identity.signing_key` or exported\n   `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY`), register/confirm the identity, verify steady-state\n   signed events across a fresh session.\n2. **GitHub Actions signing** — populate the `REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY` secret and confirm\n   `reconcile-bridge` (and its canary) produce signed events on a real run.\n3. **Gerrit-side signing** — finish canary 1787: confirm the deployed review-bot /\n   reconciler / opcert-service signs its ticket writes on the VM.\n4. **Grandfathering remediation** — verify/repin `identity.enforce_since` to the\n   flip-cutover commit and confirm `verify-identity` grandfathers all pre-boundary events;\n   add/confirm a regression test around the boundary.\n5. **The atomic flip** — set `identity.require_authenticated = true` + the pinned\n   `enforce_since` in ONE change; confirm the merge-gate enforces going forward.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] Every writer environment (this machine, GitHub Actions, Gerrit-side services)\n      produces SIGNED events in steady state, confirmed by `rebar verify-identity`\n      reporting them `verified`.\n- [ ] The rollout is sequenced safely: signing is confirmed on every surface BEFORE the\n      enforcement flag is flipped (so the gate never goes red on an unsigned writer).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] **With `identity.require_authenticated = true`, no writer surface fails.** Each of\n      (a) a fresh local session/worktree on this machine, (b) a GitHub Actions run that writes\n      tickets (`reconcile-bridge`), and (c) the Gerrit side is proven safe under enforcement:\n      local and CI each produce a signed, `verified` event; the Gerrit side **either** produces\n      a signed `verified` event from an in-scope writer **or** is proven (with file/line\n      evidence, per the Gerrit-side story) to have no in-scope writer — only non-writing\n      (`REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off`, e.g. opcert-service) and gate-exempt (`code_review`, e.g. the\n      review-bot) operations. `rebar verify-identity` exits 0 in every case; no CI job goes red\n      and no write is rejected. Proof: `authorship: {signed: >=1}` + a `verified` verdict for\n      each in-scope writer, plus the recorded classification for any surface with none.\n- [ ] **Pre-flip events are grandfathered.** `identity.enforce_since` is pinned to the\n      enforcement-cutover commit; `rebar verify-identity` over the full history exits 0 with\n      zero pre-boundary events flagged. Proof: a synthetic UNSIGNED event dated before the\n      boundary passes the gate, while a new unsigned/forged in-scope event AFTER the boundary\n      FAILS it.\n- [ ] **Signing is provisioned everywhere before the flip.** Every surface that has an\n      in-scope writer has a persistent signing key configured (local per-machine key,\n      populated `REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY` CI secret, and a Gerrit-side service key iff the\n      Gerrit-side story finds an in-scope writer) and has produced at least one steady-state\n      signed event confirmed via `rebar verify-identity` — done and confirmed BEFORE\n      `require_authenticated` is set true.\n- [ ] **The flip is atomic and enforcing.** `identity.require_authenticated = true` and the\n      pinned `enforce_since` land in a single change; after it, `verify-identity`\n      demonstrably FAILS on a new in-scope unsigned/forged event (enforcement is real, not\n      advisory).\n- [ ] **End-state:** the epic's five child stories are all in status `closed`, and each of\n      their changes is present on `origin/main` (verifiable via `rebar show` per child +\n      `git log origin/main`)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784230541601182001,"uuid":"aad6549b-6fa2-4177-9237-62e874d9fbfe"}